properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 12 at 11:23PM EST until February 14 at 4:16PM EST by NWS Jackson KY
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Jackson Kentucky has issued
a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Kentucky...

The South Fork Kentucky River at Booneville

The National Weather Service in Jackson Kentucky has issued a

* Flood Warning for
The South Fork Kentucky River at Booneville.
* from Thursday afternoon to Friday afternoon.
* at 11:00 PM Wednesday the stage was 15.9 feet.
* Flood stage is 27.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will rise above flood stage by Thursday
afternoon and continue to rise to near 31.5 feet by early
Friday morning. The river will fall below flood stage by
late Friday morning.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Warning means that flooding is occurring or is imminent.

Continue to monitor NOAA weather radio or your favorite local media
outlet for additional information. If you are in areas affected by
this forecast take necessary precautions.

The next update will be issued by 8 am Thursday.
